OL,3,C'The people that need breathing
OL,4,Cequipment should be top of the list'
OL,6,FAmanda Paul does not think her woes
OL,7,Fare more important than the awful
OL,8,Fthings others in NI have been going
OL,9,Fthrough, but she does want to see the
OL,10,Fneeds of people with disabilities
OL,11,Frequiring electricity to stay alive
OL,12,Fbeing better prioritised.
OL,14,F"We are equal to other people, not
OL,15,Fmore special than anybody else, but we
OL,16,Fare dependent on electricity and we
OL,17,Fcan't get in the car and drive away.
OL,18,FSo we are stuck where we are, " she
OL,19,Fsaid.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/9
