OL,3,C'The people that need breathing
OL,4,Cequipment should be top of the list'
OL,6,FAmanda had to sleep in her wheelchair
OL,7,Fbecause her electric bed lost power,
OL,8,Fand was then locked inside her living
OL,9,Froom as she had electric doors
OL,10,Finstalled so she can move through her
OL,11,Fhouse freely.
OL,13,FAmanda says she did what she needed to
OL,14,Fdo after learning there would be a
OL,15,Fstorm - charging battery packs and the
OL,16,Flike - and that she was very grateful
OL,17,Fwhen a NIE generator arrived, which
OL,18,Fthe team fuelled and serviced for her
OL,19,Funtil the power came back on.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/9
