OL,3,C'The people that need breathing
OL,4,Cequipment should be top of the list'
OL,6,FHowever, for next time, she would like
OL,7,Fto see a better plan in place for
OL,8,Fpeople like her who fear for their
OL,9,Flives when the lights go out.
OL,11,FAmanda said that she often has power
OL,12,Fcuts as she lives in the countryside,
OL,13,Fbut the severity of this storm "meant
OL,14,Fthat everybody was at the same time".
OL,16,F"Everybody was shouting, everybody
OL,17,Fneeded help and genuinely needed help.
OL,18,FElderly people, young mothers and lots
OL,19,Fof people needed extra help.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/9
